    public static enum BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Stage
extends java.lang.Enum<BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Stage>
implements UsesCustomNull
    Enumerates changes in the "enabling" stage before a Bluetooth LE scan is started. Used at BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.BluetoothEnablerEvent to denote what the current stage as well as in BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.BluetoothEnablerEvent.nextStage() to give the following stage to the current one.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      • LOCATION_PERMISSION

        public static final BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Stage LOCATION_PERMISSION
        Used when checking and requesting location permissions from the user. This stage will be skipped if the device isn't running Build.VERSION_CODES.M.

      • LOCATION_SERVICES

        public static final BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Stage LOCATION_SERVICES
        Used when checking if the device needs Location services turned on and enabling Location services if they are disabled. This step isn't necessarily needed for overall Bluetooth scanning. It is only needed for Bluetooth Low Energy scanning in Build.VERSION_CODES.M; otherwise, SweetBlue will default to classic scanning.
